<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-10 0423</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0433</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cold Moves East</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Temperatures dropped to the 20s and 30s in the Northeast early
today as unseasonably cool fall temperatures moved eastward.
   In parts of central and eastern New York temperatures dipped
into the 20s, while in Portland, Maine, it was 32 degrees early
today. The temperature dropped to 36 in Pittsburgh and 39 in Boston.
   Elsewhere today, rain fell on Detroit, while showers dampened
parts of Florida and Indiana. Much of the nation enjoyed fair
weather.
   On Monday, low temperature records fell across the upper Great
Lakes and the lower Ohio Valley, while new highs for the date were
set in Florida and California, including the two cities where the
World Series will be played. The temperature reached 88 degrees in
San Francisco and 87 degrees in Oakland.
   Showers and thunderstorms were scattered Monday over southern
and central Florida, Oklahoma, Minnesota, Wisconsin and parts of
Texas. Thunderstorms produced small hail at Ellsworth, Wis.
   The high for the nation was 105 degrees at Borrego Springs and
Thermal in California.
   Reports early today included:
   _EAST: Albany, N.Y. 31 fair; Atlanta 49 fair; Boston 39 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 55 fair; Chattanooga 44 fair; Cincinnati 52 partly
cloudy; Cleveland 46 partly cloudy; Detroit 48 rain; Hatteras 55
fair; Jacksonville 72 drizzle; Key West 77 partly cloudy; Knoxville
40 fair; Macon 51 fair; Miami 76 showery; New York 41 partly
cloudy; Philadelphia 39 fair; Pittsburgh 36 partly cloudy;
Portland, Maine 32 fair; Richmond 42 fair; Tampa 72 partly cloudy;
Washington, D.C. 44 fair.
   _CENTRAL: Birmingham 43 fair; Bismarck 34 fair; Chicago 57
cloudy; Denver 47 fair; Des Moines 48 fair; Indianapolis 53
showery; Kansas City 53 fair; Little Rock 62 partly cloudy;
Louisville 56 partly cloudy; Memphis 59 partly cloudy; Nashville 50
fair; New Orleans 62 cloudy; North Platte 37 partly cloudy;
Oklahoma City 63 fair; Omaha 48 fair; Rapid City 44 fair; St. Louis
62 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 44 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 39 partly
cloudy; San Antonio 59 fair.
   _WEST: Albuquerque 55 fair; Anchorage 31 partly cloudy; Boise 55
fair; Casper 44 fair; Fairbanks 33 cloudy; Great Falls 58 partly
cloudy; Honolulu 77 cloudy; Las Vegas 67 fair; Los Angeles 64 hazy;
Medford 56 fair; Pendleton 58 fair; Phoenix 78 fair; Portland, Ore.
57 fair; Reno 50 fair; Salt Lake City 50 fair; San Diego 64 cloudy;
San Francisco 59 fair; Seattle 58 fair; Spokane 50 fair.
   _INTERNATIONAL: Calgary 54 partly cloudy; Montreal 30 fair;
Ottawa 30 fair; Regina 46 cloudy; Toronto 28 fair; Winnipeg 36 fair.
