<SECOND>PM-Turkey-Quake,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quake Causes Damage in Central Anatolia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake shook the central Anatolian
province of Kayseri today, causing damage but no casualties, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
   The dispatch, quoting local governor Ayhan Bilge, said four
houses and the minaret of a mosque collapsed in the villages of
Sarayli and Doruklu. Many houses had cracks in their walls, the
agency said.
   The quake measured 4.9 on the Richter scale. The scale is a
measure of ground motion as recorded on seismographs and every
increase of one number means a tenfold increase in magnitude. A
quake of 4 on the Richter scale can cause moderate damage.
