<HEAD>Saxophonist In Critical Condition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jazz saxophonist Stanley Turrentine was
hospitalized in critical condition Tuesday with an accumulation of
fluid in his lungs.
   The 55-year-old Pittsburgh native, who has a history of high
blood pressure, was rushed to Mercy Hospital around 9:30 a.m. by
paramedics after his wife was unable to awaken him in their hotel
room, said hospital spokesman Eric Hofmann.
   He was semi-conscious by the afternoon and was attached to a
respirator in the hospital's intensive care unit.
   Turrentine's publicist, Don Lucoff, said he was unaware of any
performances the player may have scheduled in Pittsburgh.
Turrentine lives in Kensington, Md.
