<FIRST>r w AM-IRS-Hugo     10-10 0105</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-IRS-Hugo,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>IRS Will Waive Late Fees for Hugo Filers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Taxpayers who received a six-month extension
to file their 1989 federal income tax must file by Monday, the
Internal Revenue Service said Tuesday.
   However, the agency said in a statement that it won't assess
late penalties against taxpayers unable to meet the Oct. 16
deadline because of Hurricane Hugo.
   If the filing delay was due to Hugo, it said, taxpayers should
mark the top of their return ``Hugo.'' The IRS said it would then
automatically waive the late filing and late payment penalties on
all 1989 returns filed by Jan. 16.
</TEXT>
