<FIRST>r f PM-Where'stheGrowth CLARIFICATION   10-10 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Where's the Growth, CLARIFICATION,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: Members who used New York-dated PM-Where's the Growth, which
moved Sunday Oct. 8 on financial wires as f0035 and Monday Oct. 9 on general
news wires as a0406, are asked to use the following:</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In a story about the creation of jobs, The
Associated Press said International Business Machines Corp. was
offering early retirement to 1,000 employees. IBM said it is not
just offering early retirement to all concerned; it is offering
special payments to people who quit or retire at four locations, a
step expected to cut 600 to 1,000 jobs.
