<FIRST>r f BC-Switzerland-Inflation     10-10 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Switzerland-Inflation,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Annual Inflation Rate At Four-Year High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Switzerland's annual inflation rate
rose to 3.4 percent last month, the highest since July 1985, the
Federal Statistics Office announced Tuesday.
   Higher prices for heating oil and vegetables were major factors
in the increase, a news statement said.
   The announcement follows last week's increase in Switzerland's
key lending rates in an effort to slow the economy.
   The office also announced a 0.4-percent rise in the monthly
consumer price index in September.
   The annual inflation rate had remained stable at 3 percent from
May through August. Before that, it had risen steadily from its
September 1988 level of 2 percent.
   The annual inflation rate in July 1985 was also 3.4 percent.
</TEXT>
