<SECOND>BC-EC Unemployment,0097</SECOND>
<HEAD>EC Unemployment Stable In August At 9.2 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUXEMBOURG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The unemployment rate in the 12-nation
European Community stood at 9.2 percent in August, unchanged from
July, the EC's statistical agency Eurostat said in a statement
Tuesday.
   In the eight-month period between January and August, the rate
fell to 9.2 percent from 10.1 percent.
   Eurostat did not give a figure for the total number of
unemployed in August because the Netherlands had not sent jobless
data.
   In July, the EC figure stood at 14.2 million persons unemployed.
