and 528 unchanged. Big Board volume totaled 124.180 million shares
with an hour to go.
   ``I guess it's sort of a profit-taking session,'' said
Hildegarde Zagorski, an analyst for Prudential-Bache Securities
Inc. ``It's not exactly a bubbly session.''
   Many market strategists have expected the Dow average to show
some resistance as it approaches the 2,800 mark, which it has never
surpassed.
   Burlington Resources, a frequent subject of takeover
speculation, was the most actively traded NYSE issue, up 1] to 52}.
   AMR, parent of American Airlines, fell 3 to 101}, apparently
reflecting investor skepticism about a $120-a-share offer made last
week by New York developer Donald Trump.
   Among other actively traded NYSE stocks, USAir Group was down 3
to 49\, Compaq Computer was down 2~ to 102, and Mylan Laboratories
was up 1 to 20\.
   The New York Stock Exchange composite index of all listed issues
was down 0.68 to 198.66. On the American Exchange, the market value
index was up 0.36 to 396.88.
