<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Paper     10-10 0235</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Paper,0245</SECOND>
<HEAD>International Paper Reports Improved 3rd-Qtr Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PURCHASE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Paper Co. said Tuesday it
posted a 6.5 percent rise in its third-quarter profit due to strong
demand for paper and specialty products and acquisitions.
   For the three-month period ended Sept. 30, International Paper's
net income totaled $214 million, or $1.91 a share, up from $201
million, or $1.74 a share, a year ago.
   Revenue for the quarter rose to $2.9 billion from $2.4 billion
in the same 1988 period.
   For the first nine months of 1989, net earnings totaled $667
million, or $5.91 a share, up 28 percent from $548 million, or
$4.76 a share, during the comparable 1988 period. Revenue totaled
$8.4 billion, 20 percent higher than the $7 billion recorded for
the January-September period last year.
   John A. Georges, chairman of International Paper, the largest
U.S. producer of paper other than newsprint, said that strong
demand for bleached board resulted in a price increase in August
that contributed to third-quarter results.
   Earlier this year, International Paper acquired French paper
maker Aussedat Rey, the second largest paper producer in France.
   In September, the Purchase, N.Y., company acquired the assets of
the former Newport, R.I., division of Reichhold Chemicals, which
were added to its chemical business, Arizona Chemical. Last year,
it acquired Bergvik Kemi, a chemical manufacturer based in Europe.
   It also recently has acquired specialty wood and paper companies.
</TEXT>
