<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices lost ground today as many investors
decided to cash in on the market's recent gains.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell for the first time
this month. Led by blue-chip issues, Wall Street had advanced to
record highs recently.
   Many market strategists have expected the Dow average to show
some resistance as it approaches the 2,800 mark, which it has never
surpassed.
