<HEAD>International Multifoods Considering Selling Mister Donut</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Multifoods Inc. said Tuesday it
has been approached about selling its Mister Donut franchising
business and that it is soliciting other proposals for the doughnut
shop chain.
   ``In light of this expressed interest, we are evaluating our
long-term plans for it,'' said Tony Luiso, Multifoods' chairman,
president and chief executive officer.
   Mister Donut, the second-largest franchised doughnut chain in
North America after Dunkin' Donuts, has 486 shops in the United
States and 87 in Canada. Estimated franchisee sales for the U.S.
and Canadian businesses were $156 million in fiscal 1989.
   International Multifoods had fiscal 1989 worldwide net sales of
$1.9 billion.
