<SECOND>BC-UPI Appointment,0082</SECOND>
<HEAD>Taussig Appointed Vice Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   United Press International has named Joseph K.
Taussig vice chairman, UPI Chairman Earl W. Brian announced Tuesday.
   Taussig has been executive vice president for the news and
information group of Infotechnology, the company that operates the
news service.
   Brian's announcement said Taussig's job is to ``coordinate UPI's
operations within the group, and to marshall resources from inside
and outside the group in order to achieve UPI objectives.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
